---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';

const supportEmail = siteConfig.links.supportEmail;
const deleteAccountMailto = siteConfig.links.deleteAccountMailto;
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy">
  <article class="flex-1 px-6 py-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-foreground mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-sm max-w-none space-y-6 text-foreground/80">
      <p class="text-foreground/60 text-sm">Last updated: April 13, 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          {siteConfig.name} ("we", "our", or "us") is a convention game for creating a profile, registering
          fursuits, logging catches, and tracking achievements. This Privacy Policy explains what information
          we collect, how we use it, who helps us process it, and how you can request deletion of your
          account and associated data.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information. We do not show ads, and we do not use TailTag data
          for cross-app or cross-site advertising tracking.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Account and sign-in data:</strong> your email address, TailTag user ID, username or
            display name, authentication provider identifiers, and authentication metadata from providers
            such as Apple, Google, or Discord.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Profile and fursuit data:</strong> profile avatar, profile bio, social links, fursuit
            names, fursuit photos, fursuit descriptions, species, colors, catch settings, and convention
            associations you choose to add.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Gameplay data:</strong> catches, catch status, catch timestamps, convention participation,
            achievements, daily tasks, streaks, leaderboards, notifications, NFC tag registration and
            scans, and related gameplay events.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Photos:</strong> profile avatars, fursuit photos, and catch photos you upload or take
            in the app.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Location verification data:</strong> when you choose to verify that you are at a convention,
            TailTag requests foreground location access and sends your current latitude, longitude, and
            location accuracy to our backend to compare with the convention geofence. TailTag does not
            continuously track your location in the background.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Push notification data:</strong> Expo push tokens, notification permission status,
            notification preferences, and notification delivery records.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Diagnostics and app telemetry:</strong> crash reports, error logs, performance traces,
            profiling data, device and operating system details, app version, navigation breadcrumbs,
            and related metadata. These diagnostics may include your TailTag user ID, email address, or
            username when you are signed in. TailTag does not record session replay samples in production
            beta builds.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Moderation, safety, and support data:</strong> reports, blocks, moderation actions,
            support emails, deletion requests, and notes needed to review safety issues or account requests.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">How We Use Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>
            Provide TailTag features, including sign-in, profiles, fursuits, catches, achievements,
            daily tasks, leaderboards, and notifications.
          </li>
          <li>Verify convention participation when a convention requires location verification.</li>
          <li>Process uploaded photos and display user-provided content inside TailTag.</li>
          <li>
            Send operational notifications about catches, achievements, daily tasks, and account
            activity.
          </li>
          <li>
            Monitor app reliability, diagnose crashes and errors, measure performance, and improve
            beta builds.
          </li>
          <li>
            Review reports, enforce safety rules, prevent abuse, and support moderation workflows.
          </li>
          <li>Respond to support, account deletion, privacy, and security requests.</li>
          <li>Comply with legal, safety, audit, and service integrity obligations.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">What Other Users Can See</h2>
        <p>
          TailTag is a social convention game. Other users may see information that is part of the
          gameplay experience, such as your username or display name, profile avatar, public profile
          details, registered fursuits, fursuit photos, catch counts, achievements, leaderboard
          standings, and shared catch information. Report and moderation details are limited to the
          users and staff roles needed to review them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Processors and Providers</h2>
        <p>
          We use service providers to operate TailTag. These providers process information for us or
          help complete actions you request:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Supabase:</strong> authentication, database, storage, realtime updates, and Edge Functions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Expo:</strong> app services and push notification delivery infrastructure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sentry:</strong> crash reporting, diagnostics, performance monitoring, and profiling
            telemetry.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple, Google, and Discord:</strong> sign-in providers when you choose those authentication
            options.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple and Google:</strong> mobile platform services, app distribution, and platform-level
            push notification delivery.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable technical and organizational safeguards for TailTag, including encrypted
          network connections, account authentication, access controls, and role-based moderation
          tools. No service can guarantee perfect security, but we work to limit access to personal
          information to the systems and people who need it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">
          Account Deletion and Retention
        </h2>
        <p>
          You can delete your account in the app from <strong
            >Settings -&gt; Profile &amp; account -&gt; Delete account</strong
          >. If you cannot access the app, you can request deletion from our{' '}
          <a
            href="/delete-account"
            class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >Delete Account page</a
          >{' '}
          or email{' '}
          <a
            href={deleteAccountMailto}
            class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >{supportEmail}</a
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          Account deletion removes your authentication account, profile, account-linked gameplay
          records, and stored user media where supported by TailTag's deletion flow and database
          cascades. This includes profile avatars, fursuit photos, catch photos, owned fursuits,
          catches tied to your owned fursuits or created by your account, achievements, daily
          progress, streaks, and notifications linked to your account.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some records may be retained when needed for safety, legal compliance, audit history,
          support tracking, service integrity, or operational backups. Where possible, user
          references are minimized, set to null, or de-identified when an account is removed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Children</h2>
        <p>
          TailTag is intended for users who are at least 13 years old. It is not directed to
          children under 13, and children under 13 should not use TailTag or provide information to
          us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mt-8 mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions or requests, email{' '}
          <a
            href={`mailto:${supportEmail}`}
            class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >{supportEmail}</a
          >. You can also reach us through our{' '}
          <a
            href={siteConfig.links.discord}
            class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >Discord server</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
